e next week. No, she would notpart with her own telephone number. She told me to look at that clown (hewas now coming up the steps). Paradise was a Persian word. It was simplyPersian to meet again like that. She might drop in at my office for a fewmoments, just to chat about old times. She knew how busy--

"Oh, Terry: this is the writer, the man who wrote Emerald and thePander."

I do not recall what I had planned to look up in the library. Whateverit was, it was not that unknown book. Aimlessly